      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW OTIS (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (29.74) at Sandown behind PAW VORTEX in a Mix 3/4. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Capable of going well again. PAW VORTEX (7) has a strong record this track and trip with three wins and two placings from nine starts. Scored by 4 lengths last time (29.47) in a Mix 3/4 over 515m at Sandown. Looks well placed here and among the chances. HIGHLY CONNECTED (3) missed the frame but ran a respectable fourth at Geelong over 460m in 25.74. Expecting another bold showing. MINER MICK (8) is one of the chances after collecting a minor prize last time.",
